revision.text:
The '''Egyptian Geographic Society''' ({{Lang-ar|الجمعية الجغرافية المصرية}}; {{Lang-fr|'''Société de géographie d'Egypte'''}}) was established by a decree of [[Khedive]] [[Isma'il Pasha]] on 19 May 1875. Its first president was the German botanist, traveller and ethnologist [[Georg August Schweinfurth]]. Founded as the ''Khedivial Society of Geography'', its name was modified several times in order to reflect Egypt's changing political status. It acquired its current name following the [[Egyptian Revolution of 1952]].<ref>{{cite web | title = History Of The Society | publisher = Official Website of the Egyptian Geographic Society | url = http://www.server2002.net/egs1/history.html | accessdate = 2008-08-18}}</ref>

