{{Infobox mountain | name = Mount Agou | photo = Mont agou.png | photo_caption = | elevation_ft = 3235 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = | prominence_ref = | listing = [[List of countries by highest point|Country high point]] | map = Togo | map_caption = Location of Mount Agou in Togo | map_size = 175 | label_position = right | location = [[Plateaux Region, Togo|Plateaux Region]], [[Togo]] | range = | coordinates = {{coord|6|52|N|0|45|E|type:mountain_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = <ref name="pb">[http://www.peakbagger.com/peak.aspx?pid=11093 "Mont Agou" on Peakbagger.com] Retrieved 2 October 2011</ref> | topo = | type = | age = | last_eruption = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
'''Mount Agou''' (earlier known as Mount Baumann) is the highest [[mountain]] in [[Togo]] at 986 metres (3234&nbsp;ft.). Near the [[Ghana]] border, it lies to the south east of [[Kpalimé]] in the [[Plateaux Region, Togo|Plateaux Region]] of Togo. Mount Agou is part of an extreme western outlier of the [[Atakora Mountains]] of adjacent [[Benin]].<ref>[http://www.britannica.com/facts/5/517433/Mount-Agou-as-discussed-in-Togo "Mount Agou (mountain, Togo)" on eb.com] Retrieved 2 October 2011</ref> Its summit is topped by an [[antenna (radio)|antenna]].
